1
00:00:07,020 --> 00:00:08,820
=Episode 2 (Part 2)=
=The Law of the Jungle=

2
00:00:08,840 --> 00:00:10,190
Let's go grab something to eat.

3
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:10,800
Sure.

4
00:00:10,800 --> 00:00:12,000
I'm starving. I crave instant noodles.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:14,800
Don't we have any food?

6
00:00:15,520 --> 00:00:16,470
Would you like cookies?

7
00:00:16,470 --> 00:00:17,390
That works.

8
00:00:17,390 --> 00:00:18,440
Chocolate puffs.

9
00:00:18,440 --> 00:00:19,230
I want some.

10
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:23,070
Once you start,
you won't be able to stop.

11
00:00:24,310 --> 00:00:25,470
I wanna cook noodles.

12
00:00:25,920 --> 00:00:27,310
Do we have noodles?

13
00:00:28,470 --> 00:00:30,230
So who's your crush?

14
00:00:32,630 --> 00:00:34,200
Your crush, Yan?

15
00:00:35,310 --> 00:00:37,430
I don't have a clear crush.

16
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:40,590
You were so attentive to Yan

17
00:00:40,590 --> 00:00:42,080
and now you're denying it?

18
00:00:42,080 --> 00:00:43,910
He said he doesn't have a clear crush.

19
00:00:43,910 --> 00:00:44,560
Who?

20
00:00:44,560 --> 00:00:45,360
Him.

21
00:00:45,360 --> 00:00:46,240
Then why did you jump in the water

22
00:00:46,240 --> 00:00:46,720
for Yan?

23
00:00:46,720 --> 00:00:47,150
Yeah.

24
00:00:47,150 --> 00:00:48,470
Here I am. I followed the smell.

25
00:00:49,240 --> 00:00:50,590
You jumped in twice for her,

26
00:00:50,590 --> 00:00:52,000
and you were so straightforward.

27
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:52,790
The second time

28
00:00:52,790 --> 00:00:54,080
was an accident.

29
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:56,080
But the first time
you were straightforward too.

30
00:00:56,470 --> 00:00:57,630
I flipped the switch.

31
00:00:58,200 --> 00:00:58,910
You what?

32
00:00:58,910 --> 00:00:59,910
Flipped the switch.

33
00:00:59,910 --> 00:01:01,240
For the drama?

34
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:06,590
Not entirely,

35
00:01:06,590 --> 00:01:07,590
half and half.

36
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:09,400
Half was

37
00:01:09,400 --> 00:01:10,270
a bit of interest,

38
00:01:10,270 --> 00:01:11,360
and half was

39
00:01:12,870 --> 00:01:13,360
for the drama.

40
00:01:14,680 --> 00:01:15,720
You're so sneaky.

41
00:01:15,720 --> 00:01:16,400
No,

42
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:17,230
it's not that I'm sneaky.

43
00:01:17,230 --> 00:01:18,190
I'm saying this

44
00:01:18,190 --> 00:01:18,950
because

45
00:01:18,950 --> 00:01:20,190
on the first day,

46
00:01:20,190 --> 00:01:21,040
Yan said

47
00:01:21,040 --> 00:01:22,550
she thought I was a shy man.

48
00:01:23,270 --> 00:01:24,950
I think it might be him.

49
00:01:24,950 --> 00:01:25,590
Xiaofan.

50
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:26,480
Evan.

51
00:01:26,480 --> 00:01:27,680
(Day 1, ice-breaking)

52
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:28,360
I asked her

53
00:01:28,360 --> 00:01:29,510
why she thought I was shy.

54
00:01:30,190 --> 00:01:31,830
She said every time we made eye contact,

55
00:01:31,830 --> 00:01:33,310
I immediately looked away.

56
00:01:33,310 --> 00:01:34,870
So you're shy around her?

57
00:01:34,870 --> 00:01:35,360
No.

58
00:01:35,360 --> 00:01:36,870
Actually, I look away from everyone.

59
00:01:39,680 --> 00:01:40,400
You didn't look away from me.

60
00:01:42,400 --> 00:01:43,440
We never made eye contact.

61
00:01:43,910 --> 00:01:44,950
Aren't we doing it right now?

62
00:01:44,950 --> 00:01:46,270
This is a conversation.

63
00:01:47,040 --> 00:01:48,480
Not intentional eye contact.

64
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:49,510
Yeah.

65
00:01:50,950 --> 00:01:51,830
What are you talking about?

66
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:52,800
We are...

67
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:53,590
Well,

68
00:01:53,590 --> 00:01:55,190
I was asking him who his crush is.

69
00:01:55,190 --> 00:01:56,230
He said he doesn't have a clear one.

70
00:01:56,230 --> 00:01:58,400
I was like,
"Don't you clearly like Yan?"

71
00:01:59,040 --> 00:02:01,080
No.

72
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,800
It's not like I was denying it.

73
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:03,950
I wasn't. It's...

74
00:02:04,440 --> 00:02:05,590
Based on what you've done,

75
00:02:05,590 --> 00:02:08,390
it's obvious you're set on her,

76
00:02:08,390 --> 00:02:09,110
you know?

77
00:02:09,270 --> 00:02:10,190
I did what I did

78
00:02:10,190 --> 00:02:12,080
because I thought

79
00:02:12,080 --> 00:02:15,000
Yan sent me signals.

80
00:02:15,600 --> 00:02:17,030
She said something to me this morning,

81
00:02:17,030 --> 00:02:19,320
but I didn't pick up on it.

82
00:02:19,600 --> 00:02:22,670
I acted like I didn't hear
or just avoided it.

83
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:28,400
Chief seems to like you.

84
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:29,730
(Making breakfast)
He's been sticking by your side.

85
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:30,600
What about you?

86
00:02:31,470 --> 00:02:32,160
Me?

87
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,470
Didn't you think I was shy?

88
00:02:33,470 --> 00:02:33,830
I could

89
00:02:33,830 --> 00:02:35,110
have a girl liking me for six months

90
00:02:35,110 --> 00:02:36,670
and pretend not to notice.

91
00:02:36,670 --> 00:02:37,880
Have you ever liked someone?

92
00:02:40,190 --> 00:02:41,240
Actually, I have.

93
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,320
I just feel

94
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,080
a bit hesitant,

95
00:02:43,080 --> 00:02:43,720
so I think...

96
00:02:43,720 --> 00:02:44,440
Don't hesitate.

97
00:02:44,910 --> 00:02:45,720
Don't hesitate?

98
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:47,270
That impulsive?

99
00:02:48,440 --> 00:02:49,030
I think

100
00:02:49,030 --> 00:02:50,830
I'd choose a way to respond.

101
00:02:50,900 --> 00:02:56,820
(Pool Competition)

102
00:02:56,830 --> 00:02:58,080
I think that's about right.

103
00:02:58,080 --> 00:02:59,320
Why did he fall again?

104
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:00,800
But to be honest,

105
00:03:00,800 --> 00:03:02,320
I didn't vote for Yan yesterday.

106
00:03:04,880 --> 00:03:05,800
Not a single vote.

107
00:03:07,910 --> 00:03:09,240
The person I put the most weights on

108
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:10,240
was one of you two.

109
00:03:16,140 --> 00:03:22,020
(Day 1: Affection vote)

110
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,240
(Yi >Zhan, 2 weights)

111
00:03:23,240 --> 00:03:25,030
Who I'm really interested in

112
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:25,910
is Miss Zhan.

113
00:03:31,830 --> 00:03:33,390
Now you put yourself on the spot.

114
00:03:39,080 --> 00:03:39,800
Really?

115
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:40,800
What about today?

116
00:03:41,390 --> 00:03:42,390
Not sure yet.

117
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:43,550
You're so mysterious.

118
00:03:43,800 --> 00:03:44,440
Super mysterious.

119
00:03:45,910 --> 00:03:46,800
But what's the point

120
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:47,670
if it doesn't lead to a date?

121
00:03:47,670 --> 00:03:49,030
It doesn't work.

122
00:03:49,030 --> 00:03:49,600
Not really.

123
00:03:49,600 --> 00:03:50,440
No.

124
00:03:50,440 --> 00:03:52,750
You seem eager to go on a date.

125
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,720
Yeah, you're eager.

126
00:03:54,720 --> 00:03:55,720
Who wouldn't be?

127
00:04:00,320 --> 00:04:01,800
Welcome to the club.

128
00:04:02,110 --> 00:04:05,320
It's fine. I'll just be lonely.

129
00:04:05,720 --> 00:04:07,750
How long have you been sitting here?

130
00:04:08,080 --> 00:04:09,270
Quite a while.

131
00:04:09,270 --> 00:04:10,440
Are you hungry?

132
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,390
You're hungry?

133
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,470
A little.

134
00:04:12,470 --> 00:04:13,080
Let me see

135
00:04:13,080 --> 00:04:14,160
if I can make something.

136
00:04:14,160 --> 00:04:14,470
Actually,

137
00:04:15,160 --> 00:04:16,320
who knows how to scramble eggs?

138
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:17,880
I want scrambled eggs.

139
00:04:17,880 --> 00:04:19,070
Are you sure?

140
00:04:19,070 --> 00:04:20,830
If I make them, you gotta finish them.

141
00:04:22,670 --> 00:04:24,320
Go ahead.

142
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,000
Let him do it.

143
00:04:25,000 --> 00:04:26,270
I'll pass.

144
00:04:26,270 --> 00:04:28,160
We can't compete with him at that.

145
00:04:28,160 --> 00:04:28,550
Go ahead.

146
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:30,920
Look,

147
00:04:31,550 --> 00:04:32,390
this onion

148
00:04:32,390 --> 00:04:33,350
has grain.

149
00:04:33,350 --> 00:04:34,230
We cut along the grain.

150
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:35,270
When we scramble eggs,

151
00:04:35,270 --> 00:04:37,550
we want to lock the flavor
into its fibers.

152
00:04:37,550 --> 00:04:38,790
Yeah, we also cut along the grain

153
00:04:38,790 --> 00:04:40,720
when cooking Chinese food at home.

154
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,880
Exactly, so you get it.

155
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:42,480
I know.

156
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:43,320
But I don't cook,

157
00:04:43,320 --> 00:04:45,040
because my parents are good at it.

158
00:04:46,480 --> 00:04:47,670
If we're

159
00:04:47,670 --> 00:04:49,250
having salad today,

160
00:04:49,250 --> 00:04:50,070
that's against the grain.

161
00:04:50,070 --> 00:04:50,670
We cut against it.

162
00:04:50,670 --> 00:04:51,110
Yeah.

163
00:04:51,110 --> 00:04:52,440
That dish this morning...

164
00:04:52,440 --> 00:04:54,390
So we just need eggs as the base.

165
00:04:54,390 --> 00:04:55,790
It was total improv.

166
00:04:56,550 --> 00:04:57,830
Super good!

167
00:04:58,790 --> 00:04:59,880
How long will this take?

168
00:05:00,320 --> 00:05:01,160
Ten minutes.

169
00:05:01,160 --> 00:05:02,110
The water's boiling.

170
00:05:03,110 --> 00:05:04,480
It isn't on.

171
00:05:06,040 --> 00:05:07,000
It's been a while.

172
00:05:07,760 --> 00:05:09,440
We should've heated it up earlier.

173
00:05:10,600 --> 00:05:12,230
Do you like watching the sunset?

174
00:05:12,230 --> 00:05:13,230
Sure.

175
00:05:14,070 --> 00:05:15,350
I once

176
00:05:15,350 --> 00:05:17,160
went to the beach alone

177
00:05:17,160 --> 00:05:19,000
at 5 a.m. to watch sunset,

178
00:05:19,000 --> 00:05:19,920
sunrise.

179
00:05:20,440 --> 00:05:22,350
Were you happy or unhappy then?

180
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,550
It was more about

181
00:05:24,550 --> 00:05:25,670
experiencing life.

182
00:05:25,670 --> 00:05:26,950
It just occurred to me

183
00:05:27,720 --> 00:05:28,880
that I wanted to experience

184
00:05:28,880 --> 00:05:29,920
something unknown,

185
00:05:29,920 --> 00:05:30,950
so I went.

186
00:05:31,390 --> 00:05:32,390
You're a Taurus, right?

187
00:05:32,390 --> 00:05:33,070
Yeah, Taurus.

188
00:05:33,070 --> 00:05:33,880
April?

189
00:05:34,110 --> 00:05:34,790
May.

190
00:05:34,790 --> 00:05:35,670
May 3rd?

191
00:05:37,390 --> 00:05:38,480
How did you know?

192
00:05:38,480 --> 00:05:39,830
That's way too accurate!

193
00:05:40,270 --> 00:05:40,830
Really?

194
00:05:41,320 --> 00:05:42,040
Really.

195
00:05:45,040 --> 00:05:46,350
I thought you,

196
00:05:46,350 --> 00:05:47,110
you already knew something.

197
00:05:47,110 --> 00:05:47,720
I don't.

198
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,480
I don't know anything.

199
00:05:48,720 --> 00:05:50,510
Then how could you guess that?

200
00:05:51,110 --> 00:05:52,920
Just got a vibe it's the 3rd.

201
00:05:55,510 --> 00:05:57,230
So you're really into zodiac signs?

202
00:05:57,230 --> 00:05:58,160
Not really,

203
00:05:58,160 --> 00:06:00,320
but I'm good at reading people.

204
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:02,440
That's true.

205
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:04,200
I'm pretty spot-on with sports too.

206
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:06,880
Yeah, you do read people well.

207
00:06:06,880 --> 00:06:08,350
Are you upset that I didn't choose you?

208
00:06:08,640 --> 00:06:09,320
Not at all.

209
00:06:11,550 --> 00:06:12,830
I figured you were

210
00:06:13,480 --> 00:06:14,640
going for points.

211
00:06:14,640 --> 00:06:16,270
Yeah, I want to win.

212
00:06:16,270 --> 00:06:17,550
Win, yeah.

213
00:06:25,160 --> 00:06:26,480
So how did you feel

214
00:06:26,480 --> 00:06:27,600
when I chose you?

215
00:06:28,550 --> 00:06:30,200
(Day 1, ice-breaking)
The question is way too direct.

216
00:06:30,200 --> 00:06:31,000
Him.

217
00:06:31,000 --> 00:06:31,670
The most attractive?

218
00:06:31,670 --> 00:06:32,550
Yeah.

219
00:06:34,550 --> 00:06:35,350
Total surprise.

220
00:06:36,350 --> 00:06:37,760
To be honest,

221
00:06:37,760 --> 00:06:39,440
when I walked in,

222
00:06:40,110 --> 00:06:41,720
you were the first girl
who talked to me.

223
00:06:41,720 --> 00:06:43,320
Is this congee?

224
00:06:43,320 --> 00:06:45,440
Yeah, but it's been sitting too long.

225
00:06:45,440 --> 00:06:46,550
It's gotten thick.

226
00:06:46,550 --> 00:06:47,510
No worries.

227
00:06:48,160 --> 00:06:49,390
Just add some hot water.

228
00:06:49,830 --> 00:06:51,320
That works for me too.

229
00:06:51,920 --> 00:06:53,790
You were really stuck
on the clay pot congee.

230
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:57,640
Did you eat it later?

231
00:06:58,040 --> 00:06:59,510
Yeah, sure.

232
00:06:59,790 --> 00:07:01,480
Cooking is interesting

233
00:07:02,320 --> 00:07:03,950
once you get the hang of it.

234
00:07:03,950 --> 00:07:04,950
I'm just not there yet.

235
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:07,600
You'll pick it up by practice.

236
00:07:08,390 --> 00:07:09,200
Practice makes perfect.

237
00:07:15,270 --> 00:07:16,350
So, are you happy I won

238
00:07:16,350 --> 00:07:17,950
and asked you out to eat?

239
00:07:19,070 --> 00:07:20,200
Of course I am.

240
00:07:20,350 --> 00:07:21,320
Really?

241
00:07:21,320 --> 00:07:22,440
Yeah.

242
00:07:23,070 --> 00:07:24,390
Because you get to eat?

243
00:07:24,390 --> 00:07:25,440
Definitely not.

244
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,000
Finally get something nice to eat?

245
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,000
Not either.

246
00:07:33,640 --> 00:07:34,600
Definitely not.

247
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,000
But besides me,

248
00:07:49,000 --> 00:07:51,880
are you seeing any other girls?

249
00:07:54,040 --> 00:07:55,640
Have you seen me with anyone else?

250
00:07:56,070 --> 00:07:57,040
Not really.

251
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,640
If I hadn't come up to you,

252
00:07:58,640 --> 00:08:00,270
you wouldn't have talked to anyone, right?

253
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:02,720
I would talk and chat,

254
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:03,720
but I wouldn't...

255
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:05,000
Take the initiative to do more.

256
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:05,720
Yeah.

257
00:08:08,200 --> 00:08:09,760
If I hadn't

258
00:08:09,760 --> 00:08:10,830
talked to you yesterday,

259
00:08:10,830 --> 00:08:12,200
which girl would you

260
00:08:12,200 --> 00:08:13,200
have wanted to get to know more?

261
00:08:13,200 --> 00:08:14,350
I'm really curious.

262
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,480
Probably still

263
00:08:18,480 --> 00:08:18,830
you.

264
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:19,920
Don't feel pressured.

265
00:08:19,920 --> 00:08:20,950
I don't.

266
00:08:20,950 --> 00:08:21,830
Just be honest.

267
00:08:21,830 --> 00:08:23,070
Yeah, probably still you.

268
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:25,350
To be honest,

269
00:08:25,350 --> 00:08:27,270
I really value first impressions,

270
00:08:27,270 --> 00:08:29,320
because you were the first to talk to me.

271
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:31,040
What if I hadn't brought up

272
00:08:31,040 --> 00:08:31,720
the clay pot congee?

273
00:08:33,200 --> 00:08:34,030
Well, it might

274
00:08:34,030 --> 00:08:35,080
have been a real shame.

275
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:36,030
I would've been

276
00:08:36,030 --> 00:08:37,440
the one "banished" last night.

277
00:08:38,520 --> 00:08:39,590
You think I saved you?

278
00:08:39,590 --> 00:08:40,520
Absolutely.

279
00:08:42,960 --> 00:08:44,670
I feel like

280
00:08:44,670 --> 00:08:47,030
I'm the most passive one here.

281
00:08:47,030 --> 00:08:48,520
When others interact with me,

282
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:51,320
I only passively receive signals.

283
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,550
She sends the most comfortable signals.

284
00:08:54,440 --> 00:08:55,840
Talking with Yang

285
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,670
makes me feel like I've opened up inside.

286
00:08:57,670 --> 00:08:59,350
I want to chat with her.

287
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:00,640
Here's the thing,

288
00:09:00,640 --> 00:09:03,320
when it comes to socializing,
I look for comfortable environments

289
00:09:03,320 --> 00:09:04,880
where conversation is stress-free

290
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:06,790
and easy.

291
00:09:07,840 --> 00:09:09,710
So out of everyone,

292
00:09:10,110 --> 00:09:11,550
I felt sitting next to you

293
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:13,470
was the most comfortable.

294
00:09:14,230 --> 00:09:14,840
Yeah.

295
00:09:14,840 --> 00:09:16,080
At that exact moment, right?

296
00:09:16,080 --> 00:09:16,470
